title: New London picks up conference road wins
text:
New London picks up conference road wins Oct 02, 2015 
BY ANDY KRUTSINGER 
Mt. Pleasant News 
DONNELLSON — The New London volleyball team picked up two road sweeps this week on the volleyball court. The Tigers disposed of Notre Dame in Burlington on Tuesday (25-20, 26-24 and 25-16) and ran through Central Lee on Thursday night (25-8, 25-10, 25-12). 
Breanna Mettler and Brandi Allen were dominant on Tuesday against Notre Dame. Mettler racked up 21 kills in the game and Allen had 18. Emma Pry finished the game with 44 assists, and Carson McSorely led with 21 digs. 
Kenadi Schulte had a big day blocking in Tuesday’s win, picking up six total blocks. Mettler and Josten Boyer each finished with four blocks, Pry had three and Savannah Sutherland had one. 
In the win on Thursday night, Brandi Allen had 14 kills out of 30 attempts for a tremendous .433 kill efficiency. Mettler had 11 kills, Schulte had six, Ashley Birdsell and Boyer each had five and Pry finished with one. 
Pry had 36 assists and 14 digs in Thursday’s win. McSorely led with 18 digs. Camryn Blint finished with nine digs, Frankie Johnson had six and Schulte had five. Boyer finished Thursday’s game with four digs, Mettler had three and Allen had two. 
Allen led in blocks on Thursday, with three. Birdsell and Boyer each had two blocks and Mettler and Schulte each had one. 
The Tigers moved to 21-6 with the win and have won nine of their last 10 games dating back to the Holy Trinity tournament. New London will host their tournament this weekend.
